<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Several boats have sunk and multiple are 'in distress' at a Trump Boat Parade on Lake Travis, Texas, authorities said. </p>

<p>The Travis County Sheriff's Office on Saturday said it's responding to 'many boats in distress' throughout the parade's route, according to KVUE.</p>

<p>No injuries or deaths have been reported. </p>

<p>Organizers of the event had promoted the parade on Facebook, inviting boats of 'all shapes and sizes' to participate.</p>

<p>Several boats have sunk and multiple are 'in distress' at a Trump Boat Parade on Lake Travis, Texas, authorities said</p>

<p>'Decorate your boats in patriotic colors and fly as many Trump flags as she can handle,' the post read. </p>

<p>More than 2,500 people planned to attend and more than 5,800 were interested, according to the event page.</p>

<p>The parade planned to sail through Paradise Cove, West Beach, Point Venture and Hurst Creek staring at 11.30am.   </p>

<p>Dozens of boats gathered on the lake on Saturday in support of the president </p>
